communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

1. Copies of the questionnaires distributed by Illinois DPH as part of the process of collecting data for the Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System in 2024, including the questionnaires for optional modules. I am particularly interested in the questionnaire for the optional module on Sexual Orientation and Gender Identity (SOGI), but would like copies of the questionnaires for all optional modules administered by Illinois DPH that year.
2. Aggregated statistics of the data submitted by Illinois DPH to the CDC as part of the BRFSS data collection process from the SOGI module and any questions from the broader BRFSS survey that were broken down by gender (M/F/other). I do not need individual response level data.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Lena Bohman

title: Results of Medwatch Iniquiries, Sampling and Testing

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Results of Medwatch Iniquiries, Sampling and Testing
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

In the latest Report on the State of Pharmaceutical Quality, the Office of Pharmaceutical Quality wrote that "FDA is reviewing the recent increase in MedWatch reports for extended-release ADHD stimulant products to determine necessary responses, which may include additional information requests, sampling and testing, or inspections." I am requesting any reports generated as a result of this MedWatch reports review of ADHD stimulant products, as well as sampling and testing plans or results. I am also asking for the agency's requests for information, and responses to those requests from manufacturers regarding the production of these medications.

The State of Pharmaceutical Quality report does not specify which extended release ADHD stimulants it is evaluating, so please include references to the following medications:
lisdexamfetamine dimesylate, methylphenidate hydrocholoride, methylphendiate, dexmethylphenidate, amphetamine-dextroamphetamine, dextroamphetamine, and amphetamine.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Emma Yasinski
